@{jleft}	I'm the proud owner of 2 Amiga 1200s, one in a tower, the other in her original "wedge" console. I live in Wisconsin with my wife and daughter, and I'm a geeks geek. Aside from my job, which currently involves slinging sausage at a snack factory, I'm constantly tinkering with computers. This is why I'm currently attending BlackHawk Technical College's Computer Service Technician program. This will result in A+ and Network+ certs, at tech school degree, and hopefull a job that doesn't involve nasty-tasting, messy snack sausaged named after a mythical ape somewhere in Canada.


